  • Classes in swp_compiler_ss13.fuc.parser.grammar used by swp_compiler_ss13.fuc.parser.generator 
    Class and Description
    Grammar
    This class represents a context free grammar consisting of Terminals, Productions and NonTerminals.
    NonTerminal
    Like all Symbols NonTerminals are identified by their String id, except NonTerminal.SpecialNonTerminal! They are identified by identity in memory and thus must be referenced from this class, like NonTerminal.StartLHS.
    Production
    A production consists of a left hand side NonTerminal and a list of right hand side Symbols.
    Symbol
    The base class for both Terminal and NonTerminal, which are identified by their Symbol.SymbolType and Symbol.id.
    Terminal
    Like all Symbols Terminals are identified by their String id, except Terminal.SpecialTerminal! They are identified by identity in memory and thus must be referenced from this class, like Terminal.Epsilon or Terminal.EOF.
